{
  "bookId": "laozi-wangbi-wiki",
  "num": 21,
  "title": "第二十一章",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "孔德之容，惟道是從。"
    },
    {
      "text": "道之為物，惟恍惟惚。"
    },
    {
      "text": "惚兮恍兮，其中有象；恍兮惚兮，其中有物。"
    },
    {
      "text": "窈兮冥兮，其中有精；"
    },
    {
      "text": "其精甚真，其中有信。"
    },
    {
      "text": "自今及古，其名不去，"
    },
    {
      "text": "以閱眾甫。"
    },
    {
      "text": "吾何以知眾甫之狀哉？以此。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "孔，空也，惟以空為德，然後乃能動作從道。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "恍惚，無形不繫之歎。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以無形始物，不繫成物，萬物以始以成，而不知其所以然，故曰，恍兮惚兮、惚兮恍兮，其中有象也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "窈、冥，深遠之歎，深遠不可得而見。然而萬物由之，其可得見，以定其真。故曰，窈兮冥兮，其中有精也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "信，信驗也。物反窈冥，則真精之極得，萬物之性定。故曰，其精甚真，其中有信也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "至真之極，不可得名，無名則是其名也。自古及今，無不由此而成，故曰，自古及今，其名不去也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "眾甫，物之始也。以無名說萬物始也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "此上之所云也。言吾何以知萬物之始於無哉，以此知之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
